description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a friendly, hard working, motivated Deputy Clinical Team Manager to join the Buckinghamshire Adult Eating Disorder team. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a registered Nurse (RMN), Social Worker or Occupational Therapist. The Post holder will be based in the Whiteleaf Centre , Aylesbury and expected to travel within Buckinghamshire as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main role includes working within the CPA framework, care co-ordination, assessment, duty clinician cover, offering individual interventions, and the management of risk for people experiencing mental health difficulties. The role will also include offering supervision, case management and supporting the team to offer a high standard of care. Other duties will include, offering in house training, completing audits, deputizing in the absence of the Clinical Team Manager. This is an excellent opportunity to join a committed, fast-paced and enthusiastic community team as we seek to develop robust and responsive services that is fit for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dorothy Dan-Cooke (operational lead) at Dorothy.Dan-Cooke@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk or 01865 901325 or David Viljoen (consultant clinical psychologist) at david.viljoen@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk . We encourage informal visits.&lt;/p&gt;
